<section>
  <title> Velocities </title>
  <p></p>
  <exercises><title>Points Moving on a Graph</title>
    <exercisegroup cols="2">
      <introduction>
        <p>
          For each of the following problems imagine a point is moving
          on the graph of the given curve so that the <m>x</m>
          coordinate is as given in the problem.
          <ol marker="(I)">
            <li>Find an equation of <em>every</em> tangent line to each curve
            below at the given <m>x</m> coordinate.
            </li>
            <li>
              Find the vertical velocity,
              <m>\left(\dfdx{y}{t}\right)</m>, in terms of <m>t</m> at
              the given point.
            </li>
            <li> Find the horizontal velocity,
            <m>\left(\dfdx{x}{t}\right)</m>, in terms of <m>t</m> at
            the given point.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
<p>
If not given, check the tangent lines by graphing them.
</p>
      </introduction>
      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <alert>Curve:</alert>  <m>x^2+y^2=16 </m>
          </p>
          <p>
            <alert>Horizontal position:</alert>  <m> x=t </m>
          </p>
          <p>
            <alert>Points:</alert> 
            <md>
              <mrow>t=\pm2,</mrow>
              <mrow>t=0,</mrow>
              <mrow>t=\pm1/2</mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <dl>
              <li><title>Tangent Lines</title>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li><title><m>t=-2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y-2\sqrt{3}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}(x+2)</mrow>
                      <mrow>y+2\sqrt{3}=-\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}(x+2)</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y-2\sqrt{3}=-\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}(x-2)</mrow>
                      <mrow>y+2\sqrt{3}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}(x-2)</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=0</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=4</mrow>
                      <mrow>y=-4</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=1/2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y-\frac{\sqrt{63}}{2}=-\frac{1}{\sqrt{63}}\left(x-\frac12\right)</mrow>
                      <mrow>y+\frac{\sqrt{63}}{2}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{63}}\left(x-\frac12\right)</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=-1/2</m>:</title>
                  <p>              <md>
                    <mrow>y-\frac{\sqrt{63}}{2}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{63}}\left(x+\frac12\right)</mrow>
                    <mrow>y+\frac{\sqrt{63}}{2}=-\frac{1}{\sqrt{63}}\left(x+\frac12\right)</mrow>
                  </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
              </li>
              <li><title>Velocities</title>
              <p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>
                      \dfdx{y}{t}=\frac{-t}{\sqrt{16-t^2}}</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>\dfdx{x}{t}=1</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              </li>
            </dl>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <alert>Curve:</alert>  <m>x^2+y^2=16 </m>
          </p>
          <p>
            <alert>Horizontal position: </alert> <m> x=t^2 </m>
          </p>
          <p>
            <alert>Points:</alert> 
            <md>
              <mrow>t=\pm2,</mrow>
              <mrow>t=0,</mrow>
              <mrow>t=\pm1/2</mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p> This is <alert>not</alert> the same as the previous problem. Look again.</p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <dl>
              <li><title>Tangent Lines</title>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li><title><m>t=2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>x=4</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=-2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>x=4</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=0</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=4</mrow>
                      <mrow>y=-4</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=\pm1/2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y-\frac{\sqrt{255}}{4}=-\frac{1}{\sqrt{255}}\left(x-\frac14\right)</mrow>
                      <mrow>y+\frac{\sqrt{255}}{4}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{255}}\left(x-\frac14\right)</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
              </li>
              <li><title>Velocities</title>
              <p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>
                      \dfdx{y}{t}=\frac{-t}{\sqrt{16-t^2}}</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>\dfdx{x}{t}=1</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              </li>
            </dl>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
        <exercise>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <alert>Curve:</alert> <m>x^2+y^2=121 </m>
            </p>
            <p>
              <alert>Horizontal position:</alert> <m> x=t^3 </m>
            </p>
            <p>
              <alert>Points:</alert>
              <md>
                <mrow>t=0,</mrow>
                <mrow>t=\pm1,</mrow>
              </md>
            </p>
          </statement>
<solution>
          <p>
            <dl>
              <li><title>Tangent Lines</title>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li><title><m>t=0</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=11</mrow>
                    </md>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=-11</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=1</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y-\sqrt{120}=-\frac{1}{\sqrt{120}}(x-1)</mrow>
                    </md>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y+\sqrt{120}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{120}}(x-1)</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y+\sqrt{57}=-\frac{8}{\sqrt{57}}(x-8)</mrow>
                      <mrow>y-\sqrt{57}=\frac{8}{\sqrt{57}}(x-8)</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
              </li>
              <li><title>Velocities</title>
              <p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>
                      \dfdx{y}{t}=\frac{3t^5}{\sqrt{121-t^6}}</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>\dfdx{x}{t}=3t^2</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              </li>
            </dl>
          </p>
</solution>
</exercise>

        <exercise>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <alert>Curve:</alert>  <m>\frac{x^2}{4} + \frac{y^2}{9}=1</m>
            </p>
            <p>
              <alert>Horizontal position: </alert> <m>x=3t </m>
            </p>
            <p>
              <alert>Points:</alert> 
              <md>
                <mrow>t=\pm1/2,</mrow>
                <mrow>t=0</mrow>
              </md>
            </p>
          </statement>
          <solution>
          <p>
            <dl>
              <li><title>Tangent Lines</title>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li><title><m>t=1/2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=11</mrow>
                    </md>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=-11</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=-1/2</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y-\frac{3\sqrt{7}}{4}=-\frac{9}{2\sqrt{7}}(x-3/2)</mrow>
                      <mrow>y+\frac{3\sqrt{7}}{4}=\frac{9}{2\sqrt{7}}(x-3/2)</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=0</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=4</mrow>
                      <mrow>y=-4</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
              </li>
              <li><title>Velocities</title>
              <p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>
                      \dfdx{y}{t}=\frac{-54t}{\sqrt{4-9t}}</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>\dfdx{x}{t}=32</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              </li>
            </dl>
          </p>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <alert>Curve:</alert>  <m>\frac{x^2}{9} + \frac{y^2}{16}=1</m>
            </p>
            <p>
              <alert>Horizontal position:</alert> <m>x=t^{\frac32} </m>
            </p>
            <p>
              <alert>Points:</alert> 
              <md>
                <mrow>t=1,</mrow>
                <mrow>t=0</mrow>
              </md>
            </p>
          </statement>
          <solution>
          <p>
            <dl>
              <li><title>Tangent Lines</title>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li><title><m>t=1</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y-\frac{3\sqrt{3}}{2}=-\frac{3}{2\sqrt{3}}(x-1)</mrow>
                      <mrow>y+\frac{3\sqrt{3}}{2}=\frac{3}{2\sqrt{3}}(x-1)</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=0</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=3</mrow>
                      <mrow>y=-3</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
              </li>
              <li><title>Velocities</title>
              <p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>
                      \dfdx{y}{t}=\frac{-27t^2}{12\sqrt{4-t^{3/2}}}</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>\dfdx{x}{t}=\frac{3\sqrt{t}}{2}</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              </li>
            </dl>
          </p>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <alert>Curve:</alert> <m>y^2=x^3-x+1 </m>
            </p>
            <p>
              <alert>Horizontal position:</alert> <m> x=t </m>
            </p>
            <p>
              <alert>Points:</alert>
              <md>
                <mrow>t=0,</mrow>
                <mrow>t=1,</mrow>
              </md>
            </p>
          </statement>
          <solution>
          <p>
            <dl>
              <li><title>Tangent Lines</title>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li><title><m>t=0</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=x+2</mrow>
                      <mrow>y=-x-2</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                  <li><title><m>t=1</m>:</title>
                  <p>
                    <md>
                      <mrow>y=-\frac12x+1</mrow>
                      <mrow>y=\frac12x-1</mrow>
                    </md>
                  </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
              </li>
              <li><title>Velocities</title>
              <p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>
                      \dfdx{y}{t}=\frac{3(t-1)^2-1}{2\sqrt{(t-1)^3-(t-1)+1}}
                      </m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      <m>\dfdx{x}{t}=1</m>
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              </li>
            </dl>
          </p>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
