A ladder <m>10</m> feet long is leaning against a vertical wall. The
base of the ladder rests on a moving  cart. The position of the cart
at time <m>t</m>
is given by the function <m>P(t)=4+2\cos(t)</m>.
</p>
<p>
  How fast, and which direction is the top of the ladder moving when:
</p>
</introduction>
<task>
